[Maps of Bangladesh can be seen at http://tinyurl.com/bw2fuve and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5359863,63236. The Kutupalong Refugee Camp is a refugee camp in Ukhia, Bangladesh, inhabited mostly by Rohingya Muslims that have fled from religious persecution in neighboring Myanmar. It is one of 2 government-run refugee camps in the Cox's Bazar, the other being the Nayapara Refugee Camp. Its location can be seen on a map at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kutupalong_Refugee_Camp. - Mod.LL]
